--[[

				_______________________________________________________________________________________________

											  __ \    ____|   ____|  _ _|    \  |
											  |   |   __|     |        |      \ |
											  |   |   |       __|      |    |\  |
											 ____/   _____|  _|      ___|  _| \_|

				________________________________ THE CUSTOM INSTANCE FRAMEWORK ________________________________


				Defin is a light user-made framework that allows you to create custom instances before run-time.
				By simply creating a script module under the Classes folder, you can then enter properties,
				constants, client/server/request/replicate methods and events that are automatically fired
				during the lifecycle of an instance.

				_______________________________________________________________________________________________


				NOTE:

						This is the first release candidate for Defin. It severely lacks documentation and
						technical support. Use at your own risk.

				_______________________________________________________________________________________________


				FEATURES:

						-	Custom instances
						-	Custom components implementation
						-	Custom services
						- 	Automatically replicated properties
						- 	Class constants
						- 	Client / Server / Client -> Server -> Client / Server -> Client(s) methods
						- 	Server & Client lifecycle hooks on Initialized, Property changed and Destroyed
						- 	Secure Client / Server separation
						- 	Default method compatibility for Destroy, Clone and IsA
						-	Anti game theft / manipulation
						-	Organised structure

				_______________________________________________________________________________________________


				Setup:				By pressing the "Setup" button, the starting template source for a Defin
									project will be put under ServerStorage. This template is strictly used
									for development and will be omitted on run-time.

				Generate: 			By pressing the "Generate" button, your development template source will be
									structured for run-time. Automatically, the content will be put under
									ReplicatedStorage, the server initializer will be put under
									ServerScriptService and the client initializer will be put under
									StarterPlayerScripts. Your project will now be ready for run-time.

				Minify (optional):	By pressing the "Minify" button, your game structure that was generated by
									using the previous button will be minified. This is entirely optional,
									however it is recommended to use it before publishing your game. Minifying
									your scripts allows you to considerably lower their size and also make them
									very difficult for exploiters to figure out.

				Clean (optional):	By pressing the "Clean" button, your generated game structure will be
									deleted. Note that this procedure is executed when generating your project.


--]]

